    "statusDescription": "From Monday, Sept. 16, through Friday, Nov. 15, there will be weekday, off-peak substitute busing on the Danbury Branch, along with adjustments to select off-peak scheduled service:<br><br>Inbound from Danbury to South Norwalk:<br><br>- There will be weekday, off-peak substitute busing inbound from 9:05 AM and 6:48 PM. Buses will depart 10 - 30 minutes earlier than regularly scheduled trains. Bus service for the 6:48 PM train from Danbury will connect with the 8:30 PM train leaving Stamford. <br>&nbsp;- The 9:17 PM departing Danbury will operate 10 minutes later but will connect with the same train at South Norwalk that departs at 10:31 PM for Grand Central.<br><br>Outbound to Danbury from South Norwalk:<br><br>- Two morning reverse-peak trains, the 7:43 AM and the 9:21 AM,&nbsp; and four mid-day off-peak trains between 10:44 AM and 4:15 PM departing South Norwalk will have substitute bus service; Buses will arrive at stations 10 - 30 minutes later than regularly scheduled trains<br>- Two off-peak outbound trains will have schedule adjustments of 10 and 37 minutes:<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; * The 9:10 PM departing South Norwalk will operate 10 minutes earlier than its regularly scheduled departure, but will still operate as an \"off-peak\" train although it will be departing Grand Central Terminal at 7:51 PM instead of 8:01 PM;<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; * The 10:47 PM departing South Norwalk will depart at 11:24 PM, 37 minutes later than its regularly scheduled departure and will connect with the 10:06 PM from Grand Central and 10:55 pm from Stamford, which arrives in South Norwalk at 11:10 PM. <br><br>Please see our special schedule for details, http://web.mta.info/mnr/pdf/08-26-19_DanburyBusing_both_v5.pdf <br><br>Substitute busing is in support of infrastructure improvements including replacing ties, resurfacing track, welding joints and brush cutting.<br><br>Thank you for your patience while we make these important infrastructure upgrades.",
