    "statusSummary": "Planned Work",
    "statusDescription": "<div><b><br></b></div><div><b>September 21-22: Buses Replace Weekend Trains between Long Beach &amp; Valley Stream </b><br></div><div><br></div><div>Buses\n replace trains between&nbsp;Long Beach and Valley Stream for about 52 hours \non the weekend of September 21-22, as LIRR forces restore signal system \ncomponents that were damaged by Superstorm Sandy and increase their \nresiliency, and perform maintenance on the Reynolds Channel Bridge, \nwhich connects Island Park and Long Beach.&nbsp;As a result of the work, \nbuses will replace trains between Valley Stream and Long Beach starting \nat about 10 PM on Friday, September 20, and continuing until about 1 AM \non Monday, September 23. Service will be affected as follows: <br></div><div><br></div><div>Eastbound\n customers traveling to Lynbrook, Centre Avenue, East Rockaway, \nOceanside, Island Park and Long Beach will board buses at Valley Stream.\n Westbound customers departing from stations Long Beach, Island Park, \nOceanside, East Rockaway, Centre Avenue and Lynbrook will board buses to\n Valley Stream, then connect with westbound trains. <br></div><div><br></div><div>Lynbrook\n customers have the option of taking regularly scheduled Babylon Branch \ntrains, which arrive/depart from Platform A at Lynbrook.&nbsp;Plan for up to \n28 minutes of additional travel time. &nbsp; <br></div><div><br></div><div>For more information, link here: http://web.mta.info/supplemental/lirr/sept2122busesreplacetrainslongbeachvalleystream.htm <br></div><div>A\n pdf copy of the special Long Beach weekend timetable dated Sept. 21-22 \ncan be viewed here: \nhttp://web.mta.info/lirr/Timetable/SpecialTT/09-21_22-2019-LB-Sandy-Restorations.pdf</div><div><br></div><div><b>For more information</b>,\n contact the LIRR's Customer Service Center by calling 511 or \n718-217-LIRR (718-217-5477). Automated schedule information is available\n 24/7. Agents are available to assist customers daily from 6 AM until 10\n PM. To speak with an LIRR employee, say the word \"Representative\" when \nthe prompts begin.</div>",
